The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Reporter
NEW pageant Mister and Miss Supranational Zimbabwe will be held under the Mr and Miss Supranational World banner. Touted among the three biggest pageants that include Miss Universe and Miss World, the pageant will be held in Zimbabwe for the first time.  Auditions for models are being conducted virtually with entries set to be submitted online. Entries close on March 5 and to participate, one should record and say why they want to be part of the pageant. They are also required to submit two photos in colour (one headshot and one full body). Winners of the pageant, both male and female will go on to represent the country in the global competitions in July in Poland. Mister and Miss Supranational Zimbabwe founder Farai Zembeni said: “The goal is to empower young people through our pageant as they will be equipped with leadership skills and empowered through projects support.” – @mthabisi_mthire